digits(x) returns the number of significant binary digits.

integer examples:
a(i) = 0  digits(a(i)) = 31
a(i) = 1  digits(a(i)) = 31
a(i) = -1  digits(a(i)) = 31
a(i) = 2147483647  digits(a(i)) = 31

integer kind examples:
digits(0)   = 31
digits(0_1) = 7
digits(0_2) = 15
digits(0_4) = 31
digits(0_8) = 63

real examples:
digits(1.0) = 24
digits(x)   = 24

real kind examples:
digits(1.0)    = 24
digits(1.0_4)  = 24
digits(1.0_8)  = 53
